Arduino
   ↓
Serial communication
   ↓
Node-RED serial input
   ↓
Function node (count components)
   ↓
Dashboard display


The Node-RED flow performs the following steps:

Serial Input

The serial in node reads messages sent by the Arduino through the serial port.

Function Node

A function node parses the received message and increments the corresponding counter.

Dashboard Display

The updated counters are displayed on the Node-RED dashboard in real time.
